By John Austin Unachukwu  The Judicial College of London in the United Kingdom is to train Sokoto State judicial officers with a view to further enhancing the administration of Justice in the state. The state’s Attorney-General and Commissioner of Justice, Mr. Sulaiman Usman, SAN stated this after a recent state executive council meeting presided over by Governor Aminu Tambuwal.  Usman said the Sokoto State government signed a memorandum of understanding (MoU) with the college to train its judicial officers in the areas of information communication technology (ICT), electronic evidence, automation of courts, judicial ethics and conduct. Usman explained that the officers to be trained comprised judges, magistrates, law officers and registrars. 